      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FRAM STRAIT (4) wasn't far away on debut last start over 1212m at Geelong, finishing fifth and beaten 3 lengths. There was a lot more depth to that race than here and the blinkers go on, which should spark improvement. If he wants to stay part of the Godolphin team he'd need to go close here. FASHION WORLD (8) ran on well to get up for second at her latest appearance at Ararat over 1100m. Wide draw not ideal, but settles back and winds up late. Will be hitting the line hard. THE LADY VENUS (7) will be better for the two runs back from a spell and gets the chance to improve. In nicely after the claim for Nadia Daniels. YES CHICCI (10) is another likely improver worth including.",
